      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>One of the steps in the biosynthesis of uridine monophosphate is the reaction of aspartate with carbamoyl phosphate to give carbamoyl aspartate followed by cyclization to form dihydroorotate. Propose mechanisms for both steps.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcDRaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--965dce0576904b068b14deb02eced0af4eaf77f8/OChem_28_EC_008.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction of aspartate with carbamoyl phosphate gives carbamoyl aspartate with the removal of phosphate. It further undergoes cyclization to form dihydroorotate with the removal of a water molecule.\">",
